{{italic title}}
{{The Works of Aristotle}}
'''''Parts of Animals''''' (or '''''On the Parts of Animals'''''; [[Ancient Greek|Greek]] Περὶ ζῴων μορίων; [[Latin]] ''De Partibus Animalium'') is one of [[Aristotle]]'s major [[Aristotle's biology|texts on biology]]. It was written around 350 BC. The whole work is roughly a study in animal [[anatomy]] and [[physiology]]; it aims to provide a scientific understanding of the parts (organs, tissues, fluids, etc.) of animals.

